name: Tom DiNapoli
tweet: Honored to serve once again as a New York elector in today’s #ElectoralCollege. Last month, New Yorkers made their voices heard by electing President-elect @JoeBiden and Vice President-elect @KamalaHarris, and today’s vote made that historic choice official!  https://t.co/3eObCxVEh0

name: Tom DiNapoli
tweet: Thanksgiving looks & feels different this year, but I’m hopeful we will be back with our loved ones celebrating traditions soon. However you’re celebrating this holiday, take some time to reflect on all that you’re thankful for, check in on your family and friends, and stay safe.

name: Tom DiNapoli
tweet: Women, especially Black women, have been forces for change throughout our nation’s history. Senator @KamalaHarris breaking another glass ceiling by being elected Vice President is historic for every American.  https://t.co/l4UqRT4rVZ

name: Tom DiNapoli
tweet: President-elect @JoeBiden and Vice President-elect @KamalaHarris will be leaders when leadership is urgently needed. They will heal and unite our nation. Today is a good day and shows the strength of American democracy.  https://t.co/QwuXXcEZ85

name: Tom DiNapoli
tweet: Polls are still open until 9pm across New York. If you haven’t voted yet, don’t wait any longer! This is the most consequential election in generations, and every American should make their voice heard. Find your polling place here  https://t.co/wnyU8j6nnC

name: Tom DiNapoli
tweet: I just voted. I voted for my friends, family and colleagues. I voted for the 200,000+ Americans lost to COVID-19. I voted for justice and equality. I voted for civility, unity and progress. I voted for honesty, even when it’s hard. I voted for VP @JoeBiden and Sen. @KamalaHarris.  https://t.co/BWyqt4KegI

name: Tom DiNapoli
tweet: Polls are open across New York State until 9:00PM. Millions of New Yorkers have already voted early or by absentee, and many more will head to the polls today. Find your polling place here:   https://t.co/wnyU8j6nnC

name: Tom DiNapoli
tweet: Happy Election Day! If you haven’t voted yet, make sure you take time today to cast your ballot! Find your polling place information here:  https://t.co/wnyU8j6nnC

name: Tom DiNapoli
tweet: If you’re voting tomorrow and see something that doesn’t seem right at the polls, report it! Our great Attorney General @TishJames has set up a hotline to receive complaints and troubleshoot issues. Call it at 1-800-771-7755 or send an email to election.hotline@ag.ny.gov

name: Tom DiNapoli
tweet: Election Day is in just one week. How are you voting? ✔️ Absentee ballot (TODAY is the last day to request one) ✔️ Early voting (runs through Sunday, November 1) ✔️ In person on Election Day  Find all the information you need to be a voter this year ⬇️  https://t.co/NsADcPOX8I

name: Tom DiNapoli
tweet: When you cast your ballot, remember that you can vote for Biden-Harris on the Working Families Party line and help the @NYWFP keep its position on the NY ballot. #VoteWFP

name: Tom DiNapoli
tweet: Happy #EarlyVoteDay! I joined @MitranoForNY23, @mannionfor50, @MichelleHinchey,@mattmiller4NY, and @1199SEIU to urge New Yorkers to get out and vote! Early voting started today and goes through next Sunday. Remember to bring a pen, wear your mask, and make your voice heard!  https://t.co/lAsfxYCINv

name: Tom DiNapoli
tweet: Yesterday, President @BarackObama reminded us that “our democracy is not going to work if the people who are supposed to be our leaders lie every day and just make things up.” Tonight, @JoeBiden will show he’s the voice of reason, honesty & unity. 12 days.  https://t.co/V0rXwrM2Tz

name: Tom DiNapoli
tweet: The WNY state delegation is a strong voice in Albany. @RyanforNYSenate has established himself in the Assembly as a fighter for his constituents and community. He’ll bring that same fight to representing the 60th Senate District. It was great spending time with him in Buffalo!

name: Tom DiNapoli
tweet: Wishing a very happy birthday to Sen. @KamalaHarris, a trailblazer, role model, and fighter for the people. Early voting in NY starts this Saturday. Let’s make sure we add Vice President to that list by voting #BidenHarris!  https://t.co/EwGmEMqD3I

name: Tom DiNapoli
tweet: Tomorrow, Oct. 9, is the last day to register to vote in New York, and Senator @KamalaHarris gave you plenty of reasons last night to get registered and support #BidenHarris. Register, find out where to vote, and make your plan to make your voice heard:  https://t.co/6RwEwIWRe2

name: Tom DiNapoli
tweet: A vice president must be a leader who can step into the presidency at a moment's notice if needed. If we saw anything last night, it's the stark difference between the readiness of the two VP candidates. Sen. @KamalaHarris is ready, strong, and qualified.

name: Tom DiNapoli
tweet: Today is #NationalVoterRegistrationDay. With just six weeks until Election Day, take a moment today to make sure you’re registered to vote, then work on your plan to vote either by absentee ballot or in person. Find all the information you need here:  https://t.co/XMxJTSVdIo  https://t.co/GbpUSlgSZ9

name: Tom DiNapoli
tweet: That's the best way to make New York's progressive voice heard loud and clear. You can take the pledge to #VoteWFP at:  https://t.co/AWyFWijqBi

name: Tom DiNapoli
tweet: I've been proud to be a candidate of @NYWFP. In this crucial 2020 election, when we must defeat Donald Trump, I encourage voters to cast their ballots for the Biden/Harris ticket on the @NYWFP line.

name: Tom DiNapoli
tweet: We have 74 days to do all we can to ensure a Biden/Harris victory. Visit  https://t.co/1xr4lQIoFK to play your part.

name: Tom DiNapoli
tweet: @JoeBiden and @KamalaHarris are those leaders. They are prepared for this moment and for the challenges ahead, and we have seen throughout the #DemConvention that our party is unified behind them.

name: Tom DiNapoli
tweet: Our country needs leaders who listen to the people, who show compassion, who don't shy away from difficult conversations that must be had, and who believe that for America to be great, America must be good.

name: Tom DiNapoli
tweet: The past four years -- especially this year -- have exposed our country's great need for leadership and decency in the White House.

name: Tom DiNapoli
tweet: Senator Harris’s candidacy was made possible by the trailblazing women of color who came before her, including New York’s own Shirley Chisholm, who’s fight for a seat at the table led her to being the first Black woman elected to Congress.

name: Tom DiNapoli
tweet: It’s fitting and historic that at this #DemConvention — 100 years to the week after the 19th Amendmant was ratified, giving women the right to vote but, in practice, leaving out women of color — we nominate @KamalaHarris as the first woman of color to run on a national ticket.

name: Tom DiNapoli
tweet: President @BarackObama admirably guided this country in its recovery from the worst economic recession in generations. By his side and providing counsel during those difficult days was @JoeBiden. That type of leadership has been missing for four years, and is badly needed today.

name: Tom DiNapoli
tweet: Sen. @ChuckSchumer has worked with Democratic and Republican presidents throughout his career to deliver for New York. As the Senate Democratic leader, he knows that this administration is not looking out for average Americans, and that a #BidenHarris admin will. #DemConvention

name: Tom DiNapoli
tweet: First Lady @MichelleObama was spot on tonight when she spoke about how Americans know the type of person Joe Biden is and can relate to his working class roots. Right now, we need that "profoundly decent man guided by faith" in the White House. #DemConvention

name: Tom DiNapoli
tweet: Senator @BernieSanders is right: our party must be unified in our efforts to defeat Donald Trump. Democrats are fired up and more unified than ever before to elect @JoeBiden and @KamalaHarris #DemConvention

name: Tom DiNapoli
tweet: While COVID-19 was spreading in NY, the president denied its devastation and refused to make difficult decisions. Conversely, Gov. @AndrewCuomo led NY toward recovery with poise and leadership. It’s great to see him representing NY at the #DemConvention in support of #BidenHarris

name: Tom DiNapoli
tweet: I'm honored to once again serve as a delegate to the #DemConvention from New York. This week, we will hear some of our brightest leaders lay out what's at stake in this election and why we must do everything we can to elect VP @JoeBiden and Sen. @KamalaHarris.

name: Tom DiNapoli
tweet: Vice President @JoeBiden picked a running mate who is fit not only for the job, but for this moment in history. @KamalaHarris is a strong voice and, with Joe Biden, is the type of leader our country needs for the challenges ahead.  https://t.co/UUmx84BLC9
